  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.18\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : 1ff152f3a43e4adf030ac61eb5d8da345554fc5a\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nAble to install Ethstats in node server from controller server without any issues.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nDue to [recent change in Docker Compose to container naming convention](https://docs.docker.com/release-notes/docker-compose/#1230-2018-10-30), the controller server now can't reach the Ethstats container running in node server.\r\n\r\n![docker-compose](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3416976/48353982-948fc600-e6cb-11e8-87f8-a629daf3d86e.png)\r\n\r\n[Docker inspect logs](https://pastebin.com/raw/k6cH7CC9)\r\n\r\nNotice the `mypoa_ethstats_1_536797135bd7` instead of `mypoa_ethstats_1`.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nAssuming you have created the genesis file using Puppeth in the controller server,\r\n\r\n1. Install Docker Compose `1.23.1, build b02f1306` in the node server\r\n2. From controller server, launch Puppeth\r\n3. After entering network name, choose `4. Deploy network components`\r\n4. Choose `1. Ethstats  - Network monitoring tool`\r\n5. Choose `1. Connect another server`\r\n6. Enter the IP address of the node server\r\n7. Enter `8080` for the port\r\n8. Enter `n` for `Allow sharing the port with other services`\r\n9. Enter random string i.e. `secret` for `What should be the secret password for the API?`\r\n10. You should see something like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n+---------------+---------------+---------+--------+-------+\r\n|    SERVER     |    ADDRESS    | SERVICE | CONFIG | VALUE |\r\n+---------------+---------------+---------+--------+-------+\r\n| xx.xxx.xx.xxx | xx.xxx.xx.xxx |         |        |       |\r\n+---------------+---------------+---------+--------+-------+\r\n```\r\n\r\n[Example outputs](https://pastebin.com/raw/jrrtTpkL)\r\n\r\n#### Additional Information\r\n\r\n![discord](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3416976/48354426-af166f00-e6cc-11e8-8191-6959fe040e59.png)\r\n\r\nI've raised this to Peter via Discord channel and he is now aware of this bug in Puppeth. He suggests to downgrade Puppeth to a version of Docker Compose prior to 1.23.0.\r\n\r\n",
